We recommended that:

The Local Development Council and the Municipal Planning and Development Office (MPDO), together with the concerned implementing offices, in coordination with the Bids and Awards Committee, immediately look into the unimplemented projects under the 20% Development Fund and determine causes of their non-implementation. Formulate/develop specific strategies/solutions to effectively implement development projects. Consider formulating a timetable within which to complete the unimplemented projects and review the costing of projects programmed two to seven years ago to conform to the present conditions;

Offices concerned vigorously pursue the completion of the projects to be implemented the soonest time possible in order to achieve the objectives of the said projects in providing socio-economic benefits to the intended beneficiaries;

The Municipal Engineering Officer improve the planning and scheduling of work activities and manpower in order to facilitate completion of the Program of Work of unimplemented projects. Ensure that plans are accurate and projects estimates are based on standard and realistic amounts; and

The MPDO enhance monitoring of implementation of projects in coordination with the implementing offices and to submit regularly status reports of implementation to the Municipal Mayor for his information so that appropriate measures can be instituted to obtain optimal utilization of fund.

We recommended that Management:

Require the SB Secretary to refund the full amount of P49,500.00 representing the transportation allowance paid to him during the year;

Strictly monitor the usage of government vehicles by the Municipal officials and deduct the proportionate amount of transportation allowance corresponding to the number of days that they have used the said government vehicles;

Submit the additional documents supporting the payments of transportation allowances pursuant to COA Circular No. 2012-001;

Require all payees to affix their signatures upon receipt of their TA.
